{"type":"message","id":"d80ecaa8","parentId":"67f09d99","timestamp":"2026-02-25T05:22:29.488Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_015YUikkYqpP3J2JiayGn8Jy","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[90mversion:[0m gog@0.0.12\n  [90mglobal working directory:[0m /home/codaisa/.npm/_npx/82956888fae9167f/node_modules/.bin/gog\n\n  Usage of gog:\n\n  gog <script name>           will execute given script from gog's library\n  gog <script name> <param>   will execute given script and pass parameters into it (maximum 9 parameters)\n\n\n  Searching for new scripts:\n\n  gog -s [90mor[0m gog --search         starts search by script name\n  gog -s -d [90mor[0m gog --search -d   starts search by description\n  gog -s -k [90mor[0m gog --search -k   starts search by keywords\n\n  [90mBegin by typing the key functionality you are looking for.\n  You can navigate through the search results by using the up/down arrows and select the desired script by pressing enter.[0m \n\n\n  Installing new scripts:\n\n  gog -i <script name> [90mor[0m gog --install<script name>                       installs the latest version of script\n  gog -i <script name>@<version> [90mor[0m gog --install<script name>@<version>   installs specific version of a script\n\n\n  Information commands:\n\n  gog -h [90mor[0m gog --help                    will display detailed help\n\n  gog -v [90mor[0m gog --version                 will display installed version of gog CLI\n  gog -v -clean [90mor[0m gog --version -clean   will display sanitized version of gog CLI\n\n  gog -p [90mor[0m gog --path         will display path to library, current working directories as well as location of gog CLI\n\n  gog -l [90mor[0m gog --list         will display all globally installed scripts in gog's library \n  gog -l -d [90mor[0m gog --list -d   will display all globally installed scripts with description\n  gog -l -k [90mor[0m gog --list -k   will display all globally installed scripts with keywords\n  gog -l -v [90mor[0m gog --list -v   will display all globally installed scripts with versions\n\n  gog -d <script name> [90mor[0m gog --detail <script name>   will open script in browser with additional information\n\n\n  Utility commands:\n\n  gog -c <script path> [90mor[0m gog --copy <script path>              will copy script from provided path into gog's library\n  gog -r <script name> [90mor[0m gog --remove <script name>            will remove script from gog's library\n  gog -n <script name> [90mor[0m gog --new <script name>               creates a new script in vim and saves it to gog's library\n\n  gog -e <script name> [90mor[0m gog --edit <script name>              allows you to edit script in vim\n  gog -e <script name> -ide [90mor[0m gog --edit <script name>  -ide   allows you to edit script in your default ide \n\n  [90mFor updates or additional help checkout https://github.com/kublikon/gog[0m"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":847,"aggregated":"[90mversion:[0m gog@0.0.12\n  [90mglobal working directory:[0m /home/codaisa/.npm/_npx/82956888fae9167f/node_modules/.bin/gog\n\n  Usage of gog:\n\n  gog <script name>           will execute given script from gog's library\n  gog <script name> <param>   will execute given script and pass parameters into it (maximum 9 parameters)\n\n\n  Searching for new scripts:\n\n  gog -s [90mor[0m gog --search         starts search by script name\n  gog -s -d [90mor[0m gog --search -d   starts search by description\n  gog -s -k [90mor[0m gog --search -k   starts search by keywords\n\n  [90mBegin by typing the key functionality you are looking for.\n  You can navigate through the search results by using the up/down arrows and select the desired script by pressing enter.[0m \n\n\n  Installing new scripts:\n\n  gog -i <script name> [90mor[0m gog --install<script name>                       installs the latest version of script\n  gog -i <script name>@<version> [90mor[0m gog --install<script name>@<version>  