{"type":"message","id":"a6dbd534","parentId":"d80ecaa8","timestamp":"2026-02-25T05:22:36.681Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Oh! This is a completely different `gog` — it's a script manager/runner CLI from `kublikon/gog`, not `gogcli.sh` (which is the Google operations CLI mentioned in the OpenClaw docs). These are two completely different tools.\n\nThe `gogcli.sh` mentioned in the OpenClaw docs is a different tool. Let me search for it.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Esse `gog` é uma ferramenta diferente — é um gerenciador de scripts, não o `gogcli` do Google. O `gogcli.sh` da documentação do OpenClaw é outra coisa. Deixa eu procurar:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_01H41oEypUuKDLfquJEXkZ8V","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"gogcli.sh google oauth cli install","count":3}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":8,"output":234,"cacheRead":19942,"cacheWrite":935,"totalTokens":21119,"cost":{"input":0.000024,"output":0.00351,"cacheRead":0.005982599999999999,"cacheWrite":0.0035062500000000003,"total":0.01302285}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771996949488}}
{"type":"message","id":"75c60f61","parentId":"a6dbd534","timestamp":"2026-02-25T05:22:37.861Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_01H41oEypUuKDLfquJEXkZ8V","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"gogcli.sh google oauth cli install\",\n  \"provider\": \"brave\",\n  \"count\": 3,\n  \"tookMs\": 1176,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"brave\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e933cc4bbe879f8b\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\ngog — Google in your terminal\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e933cc4bbe879f8b\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://gogcli.sh/\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"26edf88730e541c0\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n<strong>$ brew install steipete/tap/gogcli</strong> $ gog auth credentials ~/Downloads/client_secret.json $ gog auth add you@gmail.com $ export GOG_ACCOUNT=you@gmail.com $ gog gmail labels list $ gog calendar calendars --max 5 --json | jq &#x27;.calendars[].summary&#x27; $ gog drive ls --query &quot;mimeType=&#x27;application/pdf&#x27;&quot; ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"26edf88730e541c0\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"gogcli.sh\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c29bc801c9259fdf\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nGitHub - steipete/gogcli: Google Suite CLI: Gmail, GCal, GDrive, GContacts.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c29bc801c9259fdf\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/steipete/gogcli\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"bdc3dd6a66cd86c9\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThe state is cached on disk for a short time (about 10 minutes). If it expires, rerun step 1. Remote step 2 requires a redirect URL that includes state (state check mandatory). export GOG_ACCOUNT=you@gmail.com gog gmail labels list · gog stores your OAuth refresh tokens in a “keyring” backend. Default is auto (best available backend for your OS/environment). Before you can run gog auth add, you must store OAuth client credentials once via gog auth credentials &lt;credentials.json&gt; (download a Desktop app OAuth client JSON from the Cloud Console).\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"bdc3dd6a66cd86c9\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b7673d35699afe90\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nHow to Connect Google to OpenClaw | DigitalOcean\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b7673d35699afe90\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/connect-google-to-openclaw\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"61470833ba7e096a\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThis command copies the file to your Droplet’s home directory and renames it to google_oauth_client.json. <strong>Return to your Droplet SSH session and install gogcli</strong>. This tool simplifies Google service authentication on headless servers. First, download the prebuilt gogcli binary (version 0.11.0): ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"61470833ba7e096a\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"1 week ago\",\n      \"siteName\": \"www.digitalocean.com\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"gogcli.sh google oauth cli install","provider":"brave","count":3,"tookMs":1176,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"brave","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"e933cc4bbe879f8b\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\ngog — Google in your terminal\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"e933cc4bbe879f8b\">>>","url":"https://gogcli.sh/","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"26edf88730e541c0\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n<strong>$ brew install steipete/tap/gogcli</strong> $ gog auth credentials ~/Downloads/client_secret.json $ gog auth add you@gmail.com $ export GOG_ACCOUNT=you@gmail.com $ gog gmail labels list $ gog calendar calendars --max 5 --json | jq &#x27;.calendars[].summary&#x27; $ gog drive ls --query &quot;mimeType=&#x27;application/pdf&#x27;&quot; ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"26edf88730e541c0\">>>","siteName":"gogcli.sh"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c29bc801c9259fdf\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nGitHub - steipete/gogcli: Google Suite CLI: Gmail, GCal, GDrive, GContacts.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c29bc801c9259fdf\">>>","url":"https://github.com/steipete/gogcli","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"bdc3dd6a66cd86c9\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nThe state is cached on disk for a short time (about 10 minutes). If it expires, rerun step 1. Remote step 2 requires a redirect URL that includes state (state check mandatory). export GOG_ACCOUNT=you@gmail.com gog gmail labels list · gog stores your OAuth refresh tokens in a “keyring” backend. Default is auto (best available backend for your OS/environment). Before you can run gog auth add, you must store OAuth client credentials once via gog auth credentials &lt;credentials.json&gt; (download a Desktop app OAuth client JSON from the Cloud Console).\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"bdc3dd6a66cd86c9\">>>","siteName":"github.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"b7673d35699afe90\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nHow to Connect Google to OpenClaw | DigitalOcean\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"b7673d35699afe90\">>>","url":"https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/connect-google-to-openclaw","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"61470833ba7e096a\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nThis command copies the file to your Droplet’s home directory and renames it to google_oauth_client.json. <strong>Return to your Droplet SSH session and install gogcli</strong>. This tool simplifies Google service authentication on headless servers. First, download the prebuilt gogcli binary (version 0.11.0): ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"61470833ba7e096a\">>>","published":"1 week ago","siteName":"www.digitalocean.com"}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1771996957860}}
